******
[4] Paraguay
Date: Sun 17 Oct 2010
Source: Ultima Hora [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.ultimahora.com/notas/368830-Este-ano,--la-epidemia-de-dengue-ya-no-tuvo-pausa-en-Paraguay>


This year [2010], the dengue epidemic has not paused in Paraguay. The
Ministry of Health could not announce the reduction in virus
transmission that usually happens in the colder months
(June-September). Paraguay has passed into the [dengue] endemic
category.

Now in mid-October, [dengue] case notifications continue to reach the
Ministry of Health from various departments [state of province
equivalent] of the country, as the rainy and hot season begins again,
which favors mosquito breeding, and therefore, dengue.

The 2009/2010 epidemic left a total of more than 20 000 people
affected by dengue in Paraguay. The magnitude was moderate but with
significant severity, because there were severe cases, said the
director general of Health Surveillance, Dr Ivan Allende.

[Byline: Silvana Molina]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed-port@promedmail.org>

[It is unfortunate to see Paraguay becoming a dengue endemic country.

